<subSubSection pageId="98" pageNumber="99" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="98.[151,1436,1146,1340]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1188,1214]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; gnathosoma large, abruptly curved and bent down near base; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[161,185,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">sc</emphasis>
) minute; genual setae absent, paraxial tibial seta (
<emphasis box="[774,792,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">l’</emphasis>
) absent, empodium divided; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae; opisthosoma with 3 ridges, setae 
<emphasis box="[695,722,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">c2</emphasis>
absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="98.[151,1436,1146,1340]" box="[208,751,1314,1340]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
